  <span id="freeText5960845203705772450" style="display:none"><i>Ravelstein</i> alternates between the beautifully philosophical and humorous to the achingly boring and mundane. However when it was at its best, Saul Bellow's writing is devastatingly good. This was my first Bellow and certainly not my last.</span>
